.TH "of_drm_get_panel_orientation" 9 "of_drm_get_panel_orientation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_drm_get_panel_orientation \- look up the orientation of the panel through the "rotation" binding from a device tree node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_drm_get_panel_orientation
.BI "(const struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "enum drm_panel_orientation *orientation "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device tree node of the panel
.IP "orientation" 12
orientation enum to be filled in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks up the rotation of a panel in the device tree. The orientation of the
panel is expressed as a property name "rotation" in the device tree. The
rotation in the device tree is counter clockwise.
.SH "RETURN"
0 when a valid rotation value (0, 90, 180, or 270) is read or the
rotation property doesn't exist. Return a negative error code on failure.
